From 758a2778fc7c80329b4951ff5b674c1a13e37b4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:08:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: add failsafe Web UI

Add a failsafe recovery Web UI for the AN7563 / AN7552 EVB,
served from U-Boot:

  * net/{mtk_tcp,mtk_httpd}.c with matching net/Kconfig entries
    (MTK_TCP / MTK_HTTPD) plug a lightweight TCP / HTTP stack
    into the legacy net loop.
  * The failsafe/ module (Kconfig WEBUI_FAILSAFE, embedded
    fsdata pages and the upload state machine) accepts firmware
    uploads on http://${ipaddr}/.
  * board/airoha/an7563/failsafe.c is the Airoha-specific glue:
    upload buffer at gd->ram_base + 32 MiB, MTD partition probe
    + size validation, and erase/write delegated to the "mtd"
    command. Destination partition defaults to "fip" and is
    overridable via the failsafe_part env var.
  * an7563_evb_defconfig enables MTK_TCP / MTK_HTTPD /
    WEBUI_FAILSAFE; the default bootcmd reads the kernel FIT
    from the boot-side flash and falls back to "httpd" on any
    failure.

failsafe/fsdata/embed.S uses .dc.a + conditional .balign and
%object .type so the fsdata blob list builds for both ARMv7
AArch32 (AN7563) and AArch64. The legacy TCP receive path in
net/net.c gains a CONFIG_MTK_TCP-guarded mtk_receive_tcp() hook
ahead of rxhand_tcp_f() so MTK TCP packets are dispatched even
when CONFIG_PROT_TCP is off.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
